          "tz": 60
        },
        "subject": "LU-7734 lnet: resend LNet messages on failure",
        "message": "LU-7734 lnet: resend LNet messages on failure\n\n*** experimental code ***\n\nWhen lnet_finalize() is called with a non-zero status, attempt to\nresend the message if the deadline has not yet passed.\n\nThe deadline is set to lnet_msg_timeout milliseconds after the call\nto lnet_prep_send() that prepares the message for sending. If the\ndeadline expires before the message is sent for the first time, it\nwill still be sent: the deadline only applies to the decision to\nretry.\n\nThe default value of lnet_msg_timeout is 1000ms.\n\nResending a message requires selectively returning the TX credits\nbefore calling lnet_send() again. lnet_msg_uncommit_tx() does this.\n\nThe source and router NIDs that used to be lnet_send() parameters\nare stored in the lnet_msg, so that we can resend with the same\nvalues.\n\nThe actual resending is done from lnet_complete_msg_locked().\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Olaf Weber <olaf@sgi.com>\nChange-Id: I1bd73b513ac76da7e4c4dc737f027f464d774dfb\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/multi-rail"
    }
  },
